<Weakness xmlns="http://cwe.mitre.org/cwe-7" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" ID="1253" Name="Incorrect Selection of Fuse Values" Abstraction="Base" Structure="Simple" Status="Draft">
     <Description>The logic level used to set a system to a secure state relies on a fuse being unblown.</Description>
     <Extended_Description>
      <xhtml:p>Fuses are often used to store secret data, including security configuration data. When not blown, a fuse is considered to store a logic 0, and, when blown, it indicates a logic 1. Fuses are generally considered to be one-directional, i.e., once blown to logic 1, it cannot be reset to logic 0.</xhtml:p>
     </Extended_Description>
